    "topic": "RBAC privilege escalation path enforcement",
    "summary": "Kubernetes enforces the RBAC escalation restriction through a layered defence: a superuser bypass (system:masters), an explicit 'escalate'/'bind' verb delegation path, and a rule-coverage check (ConfirmNoEscalation) that prevents any user from granting permissions they do not already hold. The same EscalationAllowed superuser bypass is also reused by the admission-registration subsystem for unrelated paramKind/paramRef read-access checks."
